programme.title: Come Dine with Me Extra Portions
programme.desc: In the first of four dinner parties in Huddersfield, hair salon owner Christine Wright uses ingredients from her back garden. She creates Roquefort souffle, chicken and chorizo basque and iced apple snow, but after a lukewarm response to the food, she hopes to get a better reaction to her post-dinner entertainment - an Irish jig in the front room.(n)

programme.title: Come Dine with Me Extra Portions
programme.desc: Kitchen designer and dog lover Neil Hemmingway hosts the second party in Huddersfield and hopes to impress his guests with porcini risotto, grilled haddock and tiramisu, all prepared in his state-of-the-art kitchen, which he is not shy of showing off. When the meal is over, his decision to invite his dog Daisy to the table does not gone down well with Christine Wright.(n)

programme.title: Come Dine with Me Extra Portions
programme.desc: Property developer Matt Buckingham hosts the third party in Huddersfield and prepares starters of tomato soup and chicken liver pate, followed by salmon and his home-made ice-cream. programme.title: Come Dine with Me Extra Portions

programme.title: Posh Pawn

programme.title: Undercover Boss USA

programme.title: Ramsay's Kitchen Nightmares USA
programme.desc: The fiery chef comes to the aid of a French restaurant in the heart of Moorpark, California. The pompous, over-complicated cuisine is keeping the customers away and there is an imminent threat of bankruptcy. However, the owner is vigorously opposed to change, despite the failings of his current business model.(n)

programme.title: A New Life in the Sun

programme.title: Come Dine with Me
programme.desc: Four contestants in Bedfordshire compete to throw the perfect dinner party. IT business owner Michael hopes to dazzle with fine-dining and wine - though fails to impress builder's yard manager Russell, who on his turn as host reveals his dislike of long trousers is almost as intense as his failure to appreciate the boudoir of the grape. Holistic therapist Barbara plans to deliver lots of good energy on her evening, while last to host is American Sarah, whose confidence knows no bounds.(n)

He also continues his tour of small structures in New Zealand, seeing a steel treehouse complete with automatic beer dispenser built into the sofa.(n)

programme.title: Grand Designs
programme.desc: Bolton-based bricklayer Paul Rimmer, who has spent his career restoring and renovating Victorian terrace houses, sets his sights on constructing a state-of-the-art home on a budget of £350,000. However, instead of using the construction materials he has spent the past 40 years mastering, he has opted to build his new home from wood. Roping in his wife Carol, daughter Abby and a selection of favoured workmates, Paul and his team begin work on the ultra-modern, five-bedroom build, and Kevin McCloud reveals how extreme weather, exhaustion, and rapidly dwindling funds place the entire project in jeopardy.(n)

programme.title: 8 Out of 10 Cats Does Countdown
programme.desc: Jimmy Carr hosts the comedy panel show's version of the words and numbers quiz, with Sean Lock and Victoria Coren Mitchell going up against guest captain Lee Mack and Bob Mortimer. programme.title: First Dates
programme.desc: Eighteen-year-old rookie beautician Ruby returns to the restaurant to dine with 20-year-old trainee auctioneer Adam, while 24-year-old waitress Charlotte is returning to the dating scene after being widowed last year. Will 24-year-old junior stockbroker Jamie be the gentleman she's looking for? Teresa is 66 and hasn't been on a date for 20 years, so hopes James, who loves Jay Z and Akon, can match her enthusiasm and keep her entertained.(n)

programme.title: Hunted
programme.desc: All eyes are on Ayo following a trip home to see his family, leaving him cornered in Hackney, while Yorkshire girls Anna and Elizabeth find themselves back in the Dales - unaware the hunters are just one step behind them. programme.title: Your Face Says It All

programme.title: Damned

programme.title: Who Wants to Be a Millionaire
programme.desc: Although the once-hot game show Who Wants to Be a Millionaire? had lost its luster as a prime-time ABC offering, the producers felt that there was enough life left in the property to warrant a Monday-through-Friday syndicated version. Taking over from the earlier series' host Regis Philbin was Meredith Vieira of The View. To make certain that the series would not be bankrupted after its first week on the air, the questions posed to contestants were considerably harder than those on the prime-time incarnation. Also, the famous "fastest finger" round was eliminated, taking some of the pressure off the contestants when they struggled to come up with answers. The most noteworthy change from the original version was the absence of Regis Philbin's familiar catchphrases: One would never hear Meredith Vieira chime in with the legendary "Is that your final answer?" The syndicated Who Wants to Be a Millionaire? was launched on September 16, 2002(n)

programme.desc: Swashbuckling fantasy adventure in which immortals do battle with one another down the ages towards a final, decisive encounter. programme.title: Death Defying Acts
programme.desc: My Brilliant Career and Oscar and Lucinda director Gillian Armstrong explores the final feat of the greatest illusionist ever to deceive a live audience in this docudrama concerning Harry Houdini's obsessive quest to find proof of an afterlife. The year is 1926, and Houdini (Guy Pearce) is an international superstar. Not only does the illusionist's otherworldly ability to bend reality hold audiences completely enthralled, but his easy charm finds him winning the hearts of his growing legion of fans as well. Yet behind Houdini's winning smile resides the restless heart of a tortured soul. Isolated by fame and drowning in regret over having not been present to hear his mother's last words, Houdini sets out in tour of Scotland and announces that he will pay 10,000 dollars to anyone who can prove spiritual contact with his deceased mother. But in his determination to prove that there is life after death, Houdini also becomes the target of countless charlatans, scam artists, and self-proclaimed spiritualists. Of course, stunning psychic Mary McGregor (Catherine Zeta-Jones) and her daughter/sidekick, Benji (Saoirse Ronan), seem remarkably sincere in their supernatural talents, yet that doesn't mean that the pair doesn't have their own ulterior motives for making a connection with the world-famous magic man(n)

programme.title: Remember the Titans
programme.desc: Denzel Washington stars in this powerful and moving film about the early days of forced racial integration in the US, and how a high school football team helped bring in a new era of racial harmony. It's 1971. One all-white school and one all-black school have been forcibly merged, and a black coach appointed over the existing white football coach. It could be a recipe for disaster, but the two men shares certain qualities: integrity, honour and a strong work ethic. Together they mould a group of angry, disillusioned young men into a dynamic, winning football team - and provide a model for future integration. A top class film with a superb cast(n)

And it doesn't come much uglier than The Joker, a cackling killer with a frozen rictus grin whose deadly laughing gas threatens to wipe out the population of Gotham(n)

Jerry Shaw and Rachel Holloman are complete strangers as the day begins, but that changes the instant a strange woman calls with significant threats. Suddenly forced into a series of increasingly dangerous situations, Jerry and Rachel must now take orders from a woman who is using technology to track and control their every move. programme.title: Rooster Cogburn
programme.desc: (1975) John Wayne reprises his role as Federal Marshal "Rooster" Cogburn, for which he won his sole Oscar in True Grit , six years earlier. This time out, the rambunctious, one-eyed lawman finds himself in pursuit of a gang of outlaws who've made off with a consignment of nitro-glycerine. As they flee, the violent criminals stumble across a village in Indian Territory, where they rape the women and murder most of the inhabitants. Bible-bashing spinster Eula Goodnight (Katharine Hepburn) survives the massacre and insists on Cogburn taking her along to avenge her father's killing. Despite the grim start to the adventure, Stuart Miller's light-hearted Western is shot through with humour and is especially noted for the sparky exchanges between the two lead stars. Premiere(n)

Comedy, written by and starring Ford Kiernan and Greg Hemphill, with Scott Reid, Paul Riley and Gavin Mitchell.(n)

programme.title: The Graham Norton Show
programme.desc: Hollywood great Tom Cruise, currently starring in Jack Reacher: Never Go Back, joins Graham along with his co-star Cobie Smulders. Jude Law discusses his appearance in new television series The Young Pope, while comedian and actress Catherine Tate also takes up a place on the sofa. Plus, supergroup Kings of Leon perform their new single, Waste a Moment. If there's time, Graham will also subject more audience members to the dreaded red chair - so their stories had better be good.(n)

programme.title: Josh
programme.desc: Following an unsuccessful gig, Josh is surprised to be asked out by a very beautiful audience member, and together with Kate and Owen sets out to determine whether there is a catch. Meanwhile, landlord Geoff faces money problems and introduces Kate to the dizzying world of building management politics. Comedy, starring Josh Widdicombe, Elis James and Jack Dee.(n)

programme.title: The NFL Show
programme.desc: Mark Chapman is joined by Osi Umenyiora and Jason Bell to review the action from week six, including Chicago Bears v Green Bay Packers.(n)

programme.title: The Apprentice
programme.desc: Alan Sugar has a sweet task for the candidates this week, as they make their own confectionery and sell as many as they can to corporate clients and to retail outlets in Brighton. But first he shakes things up by mixing the boys and girls and appointing the project managers himself. Then it's into the kitchen to come up with the treats, where one stressed candidate threatens to throw a spanner in the works, while the rest of the teams try to get as many advance orders as they can. On day two, the hopefuls sell their treats at the seaside, with varied success - and before long, the candidates are left squabbling on the seafront about lack of sales.(n)

programme.title: Breakfast
programme.desc: Early-morning reports.(n)

programme.title: Saturday Kitchen Live
programme.desc: Rick Stein presents, with chefs Tom Sellers and Bryn Williams on hand to prepare a selection of tasty dishes. Plus, singer-songwriter Katie Melua faces her food heaven or hell.(n)

programme.title: James Martin: Home Comforts
programme.desc: The chef is joined by racing driver Jason Plato as he uses clever cooking techniques to serve up dishes that look lavish but will not cost an arm and a leg.(n)

programme.title: Football Focus
programme.desc: Dan Walker and guests look ahead to the weekend's matches, which include Chelsea v Manchester United, as Jose Mourinho visits Stamford Bridge for the first time since his sacking.(n)

programme.title: Bargain Hunt
programme.desc: Philip Serrell and Catherine Southon provide expert advice as the antiques competition heads to Exeter, while Tim Wonnacott visits Sherbourne Castle in Dorset to look at an Ince and Mayhew furniture pattern book and an example of one of their classic designs.(n)

programme.title: Escape to the Country
programme.desc: Jules Hudson embarks on a tour of Devon as he helps a couple with a budget of £575,000 search for the perfect rural home. He also takes time out from the property hunt to sample some local drinks.(n)

programme.title: Homes Under the Hammer
programme.desc: Developers Lucy Alexander and Martin Roberts explore a former office block in Folkestone, Kent, which has been converted into flats, a three-bedroom semi-detached home in Willaston, Cheshire, and a mid-terraced property in Edmonton, London. After several months the team returns to review their progress.(n)

programme.title: Final Score
programme.desc: Jason Mohammad presents a round-up of the classified results and this afternoon's news from the Premier League, EFL and Scotland.(n)

programme.title: Pointless Celebrities
programme.desc: Alexander Armstrong and Richard Osman present a celebrity version of the general knowledge quiz, featuring four teams of stars from the 1970s. The contestants are Pan's People dancers Dee Dee Wilde and Babs Powell, boxer John Conteh and footballer Alan Mullery, Blake's Seven stars Michael Keating and Jacqueline Pearce, and Martin Lee and Sandra Stevens from Brotherhood of Man.(n)

programme.title: Strictly Come Dancing
programme.desc: Last week saw Naga and Pasha voted off when they went up against Anastacia and Brendan in the dance-off, while Ore and Joanne performed a showstopping jive that gained them the first 10s of the series - and saw the sports presenter compared favourably with last year's winner Jay McGuiness. With the bar so high this early on, the rest of the contestants will be keen not to be left behind - although with talented dancers like Danny, Louise and Claudia, that's unlikely to happen as they all take to the floor for a fifth time. Presented by Tess Daly and Claudia Winkleman. The results are tomorrow at 7.15pm.(n)

programme.title: The National Lottery: Who Dares Wins
programme.desc: New series. Nick Knowles hosts the game show in which two pairs of complete strangers team up, each battling to outdo the other by listing as much as they know about a given subject. The first couple to win two rounds get to play for £50,000 and each time the champions defeat a new set of opponents their winnings mount up. Includes the Lotto and Thunderball draws with Gaby Roslin, and Jack Savoretti guests.(n)

programme.title: Casualty
programme.desc: Robyn arrives at work in a state of panic, having failed to find out where Glen has gone. When David later finds her in agony in the toilets, it seems she might be about to lose her baby. Meanwhile, Elle offers Ethan two tickets to the hospital awards night. Caleb asks to take both off his hands so he can take Alicia, but Ethan is quick to spot a love rival, and refuses. He plucks up the courage to ask her to go with him instead - but it remains to be seen whether she'll agree.(n)

programme.title: Match of the Day
programme.desc: Gary Lineker presents highlights of the latest Premier League matches, including Bournemouth v Tottenham Hotspur, and Liverpool v West Bromwich Albion. Spurs are being touted as possible title contenders, especially after their recent exceptional victory over Manchester City, and were looking to continue the away form that has already seen them claim notable wins at Stoke City and Middlesbrough. Liverpool are also tipped by many for honours this year, and have proven themselves to be a potent attacking force under Jurgen Klopp, but it remained to be seen whether they could penetrate a West Brom defence organised by Tony Pulis with as much ease as some of the others they have faced.(n)

programme.title: Asian Provocateur
programme.desc: Romesh Ranganathan visits Canada for a family reunion and starts by helping out his seven-year-old cousin in a breakdancing performance at the local primary school.(n)

programme.title: Cowboys and Angels
programme.desc: Tommy Walsh sees the damage left at one house after a window fitter failed to put in proper supports, leaving large cracks in the walls and brickwork. Meanwhile, pest controller Ken is called out to deal with a foul smell at a family home, and comes face to face with something sinister hidden in a drain.(n)

programme.title: Claimed and Shamed
programme.desc: A tiny car park prang results in a shocking claim for personal injury, a boxer attempts to defraud Royal Mail and a fraudster is confronted by his mobile insurer.(n)

programme.title: Going Back, Giving Back
programme.desc: Aled Jones travels to Stoke Mandeville in Buckinghamshire, the home of the Paralympics, where he finds out how sport saved a man's life after he was struck down by illness.(n)

programme.title: Antiques Roadshow
programme.desc: Fiona Bruce returns to the gardens of the Arley Hall, Cheshire, where a selection of family treasures come under scrutiny. Among the items brought in to be valued are a portrait painted in India in the 1950s, which expert Amin Jaffer identifies as the work of an acclaimed artist whose paintings have become much sought after in recent years, while other finds include a PoW's diary written while building the bridge over the River Kwai and a collection of gems once worn by a duchess.(n)

programme.title: Victoria Derbyshire
programme.desc: Daily news and current-affairs programme offering discussion of breaking stories, exclusive interviews and audience interaction via social media.(n)

programme.title: BBC Newsroom Live
programme.desc: A chance to stay up to date on the day's leading stories, with the latest breaking news as it happens.(n)

programme.title: Daily Politics
programme.desc: Parliamentary proceedings interspersed with discussions, interviews and filmed reports from around the country, presented by Andrew Neil.(n)

programme.title: Coast
programme.desc: Neil Oliver continues his journey around Britain's shores, this time visiting Yorkshire and the Humber to examine the story of `Churchill's pirates' and the part they played in defending the area during the Second World War.(n)

programme.title: The Edge
programme.desc: Game show, hosted by Mark Benton, in which four contestants answer questions for the right to roll balls along cash lanes. Round by round they try to usurp their competitors in the tactical stakes of runway selection, and the nearer their balls get to The Edge the more money they bank. However if they go over, they face elimination.(n)

programme.title: Hi-de-Hi
programme.desc: The staff are called to stand in for Mr Partridge as children's entertainers - much to their dismay. But all is not lost when Ted and Spike see a tramp keeping the kids on the beach amused and believe he may be the answer to all their problems.(n)

programme.title: Some Mothers Do 'Ave 'Em
programme.desc: Frank has problems with a hi-tech toilet while staying with his brother-in-law, but the bungler's attempts to put it right result in more than a few crossed wires. Slapstick comedy, starring Michael Crawford and Michele Dotrice.(n)

programme.title: To the Manor Born
programme.desc: Richard tries to clinch a lucrative cosmetics deal with a glamorous French businesswoman, but when she propositions him, he lies that he has a wife. Now all he has to do is persuade Audrey to pose as Mrs DeVere for the weekend. Comedy, starring Penelope Keith and Peter Bowles, with a guest appearance by Rula Lenska.(n)

programme.title: Restoration Home One Year On
programme.desc: Kieran Long revisits Bill and Kim, who turned a crumbling building into a dream holiday home when they started an ambitious architectural transformation of their 16th-century farmhouse in Monmouthshire, with the aid of joiner Sam Thomas. Kieran then heads to Norfolk, where Polly and Eric's attempt to restore the 16th-century Grade II-listed Old Manor had seen them run out of money with little more to show than a crumbling timber skeleton. He discovers what has happened since and how Polly feels about the building into which she sank her life savings.(n)

programme.title: Earthflight
programme.desc: A bird's-eye view of South America, following the journeys of condors as they soar over the Andes mountain range searching for food amid fighting guanacos, and scarlet macaws seeking medicinal clay in the Amazon rainforest. In Patagonia, giant petrels shadow killer whales hunting seals, and black vultures prey on turtle eggs in Costa Rica. Narrated by David Tennant.(n)

programme.title: Antiques Road Trip
programme.desc: Anita Manning and David Harper embark on the penultimate leg of their antique hunt in Northumberland, before crossing the border into Scotland, searching for a few more hidden gems as they head toward auction in Kinbuck, Stirlingshire.(n)

programme.title: Strictly Come Dancing - It Takes Two
programme.desc: Zoe Ball presents analysis of the couples' progress as they prepare for tomorrow night's show. Including reports from the studio rehearsals at Elstree and interviews with celebrity fans.(n)

programme.title: Simply Nigella
programme.desc: Food writer Nigella Lawson shares the origins of some of her ideas, revealing just how and why they came into being, including a bowl of steamed clams with Thai basil inspired by a recent holiday in Thailand. Her toasty olive oil granola was born out of a need to have a satisfying breakfast at the ready, while hunger pangs at the other end of the day led to a dish of griddled halloumi with a sweet chilli sauce. Finally, Nigella's friends are treated to a supper of griddled bavette steak, followed by a lemon pavlova.(n)

programme.title: Great British Menu
programme.desc: The two highest-scoring chefs from Northern Ireland cook for judges Oliver Peyton, Prue Leith and Matthew Fort, who are joined by restaurant critic and Editor-at-Large of the Independent Amol Rajan as guest judge. Only one contender can be chosen to represent the region in the national finals, taking them a step closer to cooking at the banquet at the Palace of Westminster.(n)

programme.title: Mastermind
programme.desc: John Humphrys poses the questions as four contestants brave the notorious black chair in the specialist and general knowledge quiz, with the subjects being the films of Ewan McGregor, British racecourses, world heritage sites and CJ Sansom's Shardlake novels.(n)

programme.title: Gardeners' World
programme.desc: At Longmeadow, Monty Don gives advice on the plants that need winter protection and thinks ahead to colourful spring bouquets by planting bulbs in the cutting garden. Carol Klein heads to Worcestershire in search of some autumn colour, in a garden designed to reach its peak of flowering in October. Frances Tophill finds out whether there is a north-south divide in the yield and taste of vegetables grown at RHS Rosemoor in Devon and RHS Harlow Carr in Yorkshire, while Zephaniah Lindo investigates the relationship between roots and microscopic fungi. Plus, Nick Bailey injects new life into a small, neglected garden in London, and Alan Power spends a day in the gardens of Mount Stewart near Belfast. Includes Gardeners' World Weather.(n)

programme.title: The Great British Bake Off: An Extra Slice
programme.desc: Reigning Bake Off champion Nadiya Hussain and Scottish Conservative Party leader Ruth Davidson are among those joining host Jo Brand to discuss the semi-final stage of the contest. Plus, unseen footage from the programme and an interview with the contestant who was evicted from the tent on Wednesday.(n)

programme.title: QI
programme.desc: New series. Sandi Toksvig takes over as host, inviting panellists Alan Davies, Cariad Lloyd, Romesh Ranganathan and Phill Jupitus to answer questions on subjects associated with the letter n. Since the questions are impossible to answer, points are awarded for being interesting rather than correct.(n)

programme.title: Newsnight
programme.desc: Analysis of the day's events, presented by James O'Brien.(n)

programme.title: Later - with Jools Holland
programme.desc: Extended edition of the music programme. Making their debut on the show a mere 57 years after they launched are vocal harmony legends the Temptations, who are still lead by original member Otis Williams. Williams' Temps will reprise a couple of their classic hits around Jools' piano. Plus, LA-based singer songwriter KT Tunstall, plays a song from her recent album, Kin. Also appearing are Stax-influenced Alabama band St Paul and the Broken Bones, London electro-pop four piece Teleman, Minnesota-based singer-songwriter Haley Bonar and Let's Eat Grandma, an experimental pop outfit from Norwich.(n)

programme.title: The Secret Life of Sue Townsend (Aged 68 3/4)
programme.desc: Julie Walters narrates a profile of the author and creator of Adrian Mole. Sue Townsend left school at 14 with no qualifications, and was struggling to support three children when her writing career began. The critical and commercial success of the first Adrian Mole book led to her becoming one of the best-selling writers of the 1980s. Featuring contributions from friends, family, comedians and writers she inspired, and pupils at her former school, as well as entries from her own diary, documenting her struggles with ill health.(n)

programme.title: Question Time
programme.desc: David Dimbleby chairs a debate from Hartlepool. The panel comprises of former Chancellor Kenneth Clarke, Shadow Education Secretary Angela Rayner, runner-up in the Ukip leadership election Lisa Duffy, former Greek finance minister Yanis Varoufakis and the previous owner of the Daily Telegraph Conrad Black.(n)

programme.title: Horizon
programme.sub-title: Jimmy Carr and the Science of Laughter - A Horizon Special.
programme.desc: The comedian takes over the science programme in a special episode for BBC's sitcom season, turning it into a chat show with eminent scientists as guests. He talks to them about the nature of laughter, with the studio audiences serving as guinea pigs in his attempt to get to the bottom of what laughter is, what it has to do with comedy, and why human beings find it a pleasurable sensation. The programme reveals that laughter predates the human species and may have played a vital role in our evolution.(n)

programme.title: This Is BBC Two
programme.desc: Preview of upcoming programmes from BBC Two.(n)

programme.title: Flight for Freedom
programme.desc: A female pilot in the 1930s strives to overturn prejudices against women in the aviation establishment by carrying out a series of record-breaking flights. Her talents attract the attention of the US government, who enlist her help in carrying out a dangerous secret mission. Drama, starring Rosalind Russell and Fred MacMurray.(n)

programme.title: Wonder Man
programme.desc: Nightclub entertainer Buzzy Bellew witnesses a murder committed by gangster Ten Grand Jackson and is killed by two of his thugs. Buzzy comes back as a ghost and tries to persuade his bookish twin Edwin Dingle to avenge his death by helping the police catch Jackson. Comedy musical, starring Danny Kaye, Virginia Mayo, Vera-Ellen, Donald Woods and Steve Cochran.(n)

programme.title: Natural World
programme.sub-title: Natural World: Heligan - Secrets of the Lost Garden.
programme.desc: The secret lives of the wildlife in the popular Cornish tourist attraction, set against the background of the gardening year. Charlie Hamilton James shoots footage highlighting a variety of creatures inhabiting the estate, including foxes at play in the pleasure gardens after the visitors have left, toads mating and the badgers that enter the tea rooms at night. Narrated by Philippa Forrester.(n)

programme.title: Lost Land of the Jaguar
programme.desc: Steve Backshall reaches the summit of a table-top mountain, after climbing a vertical cliff face nearly as high as the Empire State Building. Meanwhile, Dr George McGavin and Gordon Buchanan have to haul three boats and all their kit through the jungle after finding the rapids of the Rewa River impassable. At the end of the journey, George presents a report on the expedition to the President of Guyana, Bharrat Jagdeo. Last in the series.(n)

programme.title: Antiques Road Trip
programme.desc: Experts Anita Manning and David Harper embark on the last leg of their journey, travelling from Ayrshire to the Isle of Bute, Glasgow, Renfrewshire and ending at an auction in Paisley. They both take risks in a bid to win the week, but it remains to be seen who will come out on top.(n)

programme.title: Great British Menu
programme.desc: The first of the Northern Ireland heats sees returning contender Chris McGowan and newcomers Mark Abbott and Eddie Attwell prepare their starters for the banquet. There are some varied and exciting dishes as the chefs get creative with pig's heads and potatoes, as well as a reinvention of the classic ploughman's, while there is real shock and emotion when the veteran judge delivers his scores.(n)

programme.title: Great British Menu
programme.desc: The Northern Ireland chefs attempt to impress the judges with their fish courses. Mark Abbott is pushing himself again, plating up a complex fish course of the very finest produce - but at the last minute forgets a key element. Returning chef Chris McGowan refines cod and chips, while Eddie Attwell is getting classical with the king of the sea turbot. The repartee is relentless as the chefs jostle for top place on the leader board and once again there is plenty of emotion as veteran chef Michael O'Hare delivers the scores.(n)

programme.title: Great British Menu
programme.desc: The chefs from the Northern Ireland category turn their attention to main courses, as returning contestant Chris McGowan sets himself the challenge of making his own venison sausages to serve with a venison rack. Eddie Attwell also opts for venison, serving it with a traditional Northern Ireland dish called Dock pudding. Finally, Mark Abbott once again decides to push himself to the limit with a wagyu beef dish served with tongue and corn.(n)

programme.title: Talking Pictures
programme.desc: A look at the TV appearances made over the years by Swedish Academy Award-winning actress Ingrid Bergman, exploring the milestones of her life and career, including her appearances in Casablanca and Spellbound. Narrated by Sylvia Syms.(n)

programme.title: Notorious
programme.desc: An undercover agent falls for the socialite daughter of a convicted German spy and persuades her to feed him information about the activities of a group of Nazi collaborators in Brazil - a dangerous decision that threatens to cost the girl her life as the leader of the gang draws closer to uncovering her secret. Alfred Hitchcock's thriller, starring Cary Grant, Ingrid Bergman, Claude Rains and Louis Calhern.(n)

programme.title: Flog It
programme.desc: Members of the public gather at the Imperial War Museum Duxford in Cambridgeshire to present their antiques to James Lewis and Christina Trevanion. Presented by Paul Martin.(n)

programme.title: Nature's Weirdest Events
programme.desc: Chris Packham presents more mysteries and strange stories, including the strange balls of worms that turned up on a road, fish stuck in fences in Texas and how an Australian town became plagued by giant bats. Plus, why so many sperm whales became stranded around the North Sea in 2015, how a robot could help save the Great Barrier Reef and how a spider in the Sahara could help take humans to other planets.(n)

programme.title: Gardeners' World
programme.desc: At Longmeadow, Monty Don gives advice on the plants that need winter protection and thinks ahead to colourful spring bouquets by planting bulbs in the cutting garden. Carol Klein heads to Worcestershire in search of some autumn colour, in a garden designed to reach its peak of flowering in October. Frances Tophill finds out whether there is a north-south divide in the yield and taste of vegetables grown at RHS Rosemoor in Devon and RHS Harlow Carr in Yorkshire, while Zephaniah Lindo investigates the relationship between roots and microscopic fungi. Plus, Nick Bailey injects new life into a small, neglected garden in London, and Alan Power spends a day in the gardens of Mount Stewart near Belfast. Includes Gardeners' World Weather.(n)

programme.title: Iolo's Great Welsh Parks
programme.desc: Naturalist Iolo Williams explores historic estates and parklands, examining their role in protecting wildlife and meeting those with inside knowledge. He uses his expertise to locate nocturnal creatures in areas which are open to public access but where natural activity often goes unnoticed.(n)

programme.title: Inside the Commons
programme.desc: Michael Cockerell witnesses battles breaking out over the future of the House as Speaker John Bercow runs into trouble with his own plans for reforming it, while Tory backbencher Zac Goldsmith tries to get voters the power to sack their MPs. Plus, an insight into the challenges of carrying out a multi-billion-pound programme of restoration work while Parliament is sitting, and the events and banqueting team tries to raise money for the upkeep of the palace by hosting fashion shows and film premieres inside the House. Last in the series.(n)

programme.title: The Great British Bake Off: An Extra Slice
programme.desc: Reigning Bake Off champion Nadiya Hussain and Scottish Conservative Party leader Ruth Davidson are among those joining host Jo Brand to discuss the semi-final stage of the contest. Plus, unseen footage from the programme and an interview with the contestant who was evicted from the tent on Wednesday.(n)

programme.title: Dad's Army
programme.desc: Captain Mainwaring and his platoon plan to stage a re-enactment of the St George and the dragon story as part of the Wings for Victory fundraising campaign, but discover Hodges and his fellow ARP wardens have had the same idea. Vintage comedy first shown in 1977, starring Arthur Lowe.(n)

programme.title: The School That Got Teens Reading
programme.desc: Documentary charting one Lancashire school's efforts to inspire reluctant teenagers to take up reading for pleasure. Despite receiving otherwise outstanding Ofsted reports, Ripley Academy in Lancaster has been struggling to engage its pupils in one of the most important academic skills. Having exhausted every other technique across hundreds of books, the staff turn to comedian Javone Prince and Blue Peter's Helen Skelton for help in convincing their most reluctant readers to take the plunge.(n)

programme.title: The Invisible Woman
programme.desc: Premiere. A Victorian teacher recalls her former life as an actress, and her relationship with Charles Dickens. She quickly becomes his lover and the inspiration for his work, but the strain of keeping their affair a secret takes its toll on her. Fact-based period drama, directed by and starring Ralph Fiennes, with Felicity Jones and Kristin Scott Thomas.(n)

programme.title: Artsnight
programme.desc: Author and comedian David Baddiel introduces this year's Man Booker Prize shortlist, which provides readers with a view on the very best recent works of fiction available in the English-speaking world. Himself a former Booker Prize judge, Baddiel names the six novels chosen by this year's panel, which consists of Jon Day, Abdulrazak Gurnah, David Harsent and Olivia Williams, and is chaired by Amanda Foreman. Plus, reviewers including Mariella Frostrup, Val McDermid and George `the Poet' Mpanga meet some of the nominated authors, and take a look at the stories and themes covered in the shortlisted entries.(n)

programme.title: Revolutionary Road
programme.desc: Married couple Frank and April Wheeler live a picture-perfect life on the surface, but in truth are growing frustrated with their lot and feel stifled by their situation. When April suggests the family moves to France to start a new life, Frank is persuaded it is a good idea, though when he is offered a stable job with a lucrative pay packet he changes his mind, leaving April a desperate figure longing for an escape. Sam Mendes' 1950s-set drama, starring Kate Winslet, Leonardo DiCaprio, Michael Shannon and Kathy Bates.(n)

programme.title: World News Today
programme.desc: The day's leading stories.(n)

programme.title: Top of the Pops: 1982
programme.desc: An edition first broadcast on July 1 1982, in which John Peel introduces performances by Natasha, Captain Sensible, Visage, Queen, Midge Ure, the Jam and Dollar. Plus, a dance routine by Zoo.(n)

programme.title: The Good Old Days
programme.desc: A 1976 edition of the old-time music hall programme, chaired by Leonard Sachs. Danny La Rue, Dorothy Ross, Francis Van Dyke and members of the Players Theatre, London entertain an audience from the stage of the Leeds City Varieties. First aired January 29 1976.(n)

programme.title: Pink Floyd Beginnings 1967 - 1972
programme.desc: After The Dark Side of the Moon became a global smash in 1973, rock band Pink Floyd concentrated on the creative freedom of live performance, leaving the world of TV behind. Now, after painstaking research, tapes of some early historic appearances have been tracked down and compiled, offering an insight into Floyd's initial work, and providing clues as to the origins of their later material.(n)

programme.title: Totally 60s Psychedelic Rock at the BBC
programme.desc: A compilation of the genre from programmes such as Colour Me Pop, How It Is, Top of the Pops and Once More with Felix. Performers include Status Quo, the Incredible String Band, Donovan, the Bonzo Dog Doo-Dah Band, Julie Driscoll with Brian Auger and the Trinity, the Moody Blues, the Crazy World of Arthur Brown, Joe Cocker, the Move, Procol Harum, Cream, Jimi Hendrix and the Who.(n)

programme.title: Genesis: Together & Apart
programme.desc: Many schoolboys get together to form a band, but few of them go on to become multi-million-selling recording artists - but that's what happened to Genesis. Its core members - Peter Gabriel, Mike Rutherford and Tony Banks - met at Charterhouse, a public school in Surrey, and began playing together with two other students in 1967. A few years and personnel changes later (including the addition of drummer Phil Collins) and the classic line-up was in place. But relationships within the band were fraught; Gabriel left for a solo career in 1975, and Rutherford, Collins, Banks and Steve Hackett carried on without him. Here, they're back together again to discuss their careers. Rare archive footage helps tell the story.(n)

programme.title: Top of the Pops: 1982
programme.desc: An edition first broadcast on July 1 1982, in which John Peel introduces performances by Natasha, Captain Sensible, Visage, Queen, Midge Ure, the Jam and Dollar. Plus, a dance routine by Zoo.(n)

programme.title: Pink Floyd Beginnings 1967 - 1972
programme.desc: After The Dark Side of the Moon became a global smash in 1973, rock band Pink Floyd concentrated on the creative freedom of live performance, leaving the world of TV behind. Now, after painstaking research, tapes of some early historic appearances have been tracked down and compiled, offering an insight into Floyd's initial work, and providing clues as to the origins of their later material.(n)

programme.title: Totally 60s Psychedelic Rock at the BBC
programme.desc: A compilation of the genre from programmes such as Colour Me Pop, How It Is, Top of the Pops and Once More with Felix. Performers include Status Quo, the Incredible String Band, Donovan, the Bonzo Dog Doo-Dah Band, Julie Driscoll with Brian Auger and the Trinity, the Moody Blues, the Crazy World of Arthur Brown, Joe Cocker, the Move, Procol Harum, Cream, Jimi Hendrix and the Who.(n)

programme.title: Prog Rock at the BBC
programme.desc: Footage from the BBC studios of some of Britain's most popular progressive rock bands dating back to the early 1970s. Including performances by Emerson, Lake and Palmer, Yes, Genesis, Caravan, Barclay James Harvest, Gentle Giant, Family and Atomic Rooster.(n)

programme.title: Lost Kingdoms of South America
programme.desc: The series revealing the character of South America's ancient peoples concludes as Dr Jago Cooper investigates the rise and fall of Chimor, the continent's first empire. In the spectacular deserts of Peru, the archaeologist explores the vast ruins of a lost city, and learns how the inhabitants once thrived in an extreme climate. He also takes a look at the customs and rituals of the civilisation, in which people made shocking sacrifices to their gods under the watchful eye of an all-powerful monarchy. Last in the series.(n)

programme.title: The Incredible Human Journey
programme.desc: Dr Alice Roberts visits Asia on her quest to discover how a small band of humans came to eventually populate the globe. In Siberia, one of the most inhospitable places on Earth, she meets the Evenki nomads, a remote tribe that has much to teach the world about surviving in extreme climates. Alice also considers the claim that the Chinese do not share the same African ancestry as other peoples.(n)

programme.title: The Code
programme.desc: New series. Jesse and Ned are confronted with the daunting possibility of being extradited to the US to face criminal charges. Fortunately for the Banks brothers, Australian National Security is dealing with an explosive case they cannot crack, and Jesse might be the man they need. Australian thriller, starring Dan Spielman and Ashley Zukerman. Anthony LaPaglia joins the cast as the elusive internet baron Jan Roth.(n)

programme.title: The Code
programme.desc: After being kidnapped by Roth, Jesse and Hani disappear into the jungles of West Papua. Jesse reluctantly makes a deal with the man nobody trusts, hoping his decision will buy them enough time to find the data the authorities need. Australian thriller, starring Ashley Zukerman, Adele Perovic and Anthony LaPaglia.(n)

programme.title: Meat Loaf: In and Out of Hell
programme.desc: A profile of the rock star's life and career, reflecting on the music that propelled him to fame and charting his journey from an overweight, bullied child to his larger-than-life persona and icon status. Featuring an interview and performance by the singer, as well as backstage footage from a Las Vegas concert. The film also revisits the Dallas of Meat Loaf's early years and includes insights from high school friends who reveal where the unusual moniker really came from.(n)

programme.title: Heavy Metal Britannia

programme.title: American Justice
programme.desc: Murder on a Reservation. A hidden war of words rages on in the A&E program American Justice: Murder on a Reservation. Leonard Peltier is one of the most well-known political prisoners in America. Serving two life sentences for the murders of federal agents in 1975, the Nobel Peace Prize nominee maintains his innocence while blasting the intimidating techniques of the U.S. government. The shootout which put him in prison is known as "the Incident at Oglala" and has roots going back to the massacre at Wounded Knee. Peltier claims he is serving time for his radical views on Native American rights while the government thinks it has finally tamed a violent troublemaker. But, beyond the political ramifications, Peltier's case is full of inconsistencies. There are no witnesses or physical evidence to identify Peltier as the shooter. During his trial, he was deprived of crucial background testimony which established the FBI's reign of terror over the South Dakota reservation. Peltier continues his appeal for justice while many are left wondering what really happened that fateful day(n)

programme.title: Regarding Henry
programme.desc: Combining elements of A Christmas Carol and Rain Man (1988), this modern-day parable of greed and redemption was crafted with generous helpings of sentimentality by director Mike Nicholas. Harrison Ford stars as Henry Turner, a slick, ruthless corporate attorney willing to spin any falsehood to win a case. A bully to his teenage daughter Rachel (Mikki Allen), Henry also cheats on his wife Sarah (Annette Bening) and treats everyone from the maid to his assistant with cruel selfishness. Stepping out to a local mini-market for a pack of cigarettes late one night, Henry accidentally interrupts a burglary and is shot in the head by a stick-up artist. After a long coma, Henry survives only to find that he has no memory and must re-learn everything from reading to tying his shoes. Reborn as a friendly, childlike innocent, Henry charms his therapist (Bill Nunn) and reconnects with his wife and daughter, only to uncover some secrets about how truly appalling he once was(n)

programme.title: Transporter 2
programme.desc: Frank Martin is back as the Transporter, who'll take anything anywhere, no questions asked, for the right money. This time, he's earning what should be easy money guarding the son of government drugs czar Billings. But when the boy is kidnapped by drugs lord Gianni, Martin takes it as a professional slur and sets out to find the boy and the baddies in Louis Leterrier's all-action film co-written by Luc Besson(n)

programme.title: Extreme Measures
programme.desc: Intelligent thriller about an idealistic young doctor (Hugh Grant) who uncovers a sinister world of illegal medical experiments. Dr Guy Luthan (Grant) is working through another hard shift in the emergency room when he treats a delusional, homeless patient who exhibits wildly erratic and unfamiliar symptoms. To add to the mystery, the man is naked, except for a medical bracelet on his wrist that can only have come from another hospital. Luthan is unable to save the patient, but neither can he forget the unusual circumstances surrounding the man's arrival. He resolves to look into the case further, but when he looks for the autopsy report he finds that it is missing - and so is the body. Unwilling to let the matter drop, despite strong urging from his superiors at the hospital, Luthan continues to search for answers. As this search progresses, he experiences more bad 'luck': his apartment is broken into and he is loses his job. Clearly somebody wants him to stop his investigation. Undeterred, Luthan pursues the truth, and the trail leads to internationally renowned neurologist Dr. Lawrence Myrick (Gene Hackman), acclaimed for his research into regenerating spinal tissue. Myrick's research has the potential to change the world for countless victims of spinal injury - but does this excuse the terrible price being paid by innocent victims?(n)

programme.title: The Prophecy: Uprising
programme.desc: If you think the prophesies have all been written and humankind's fate forever sealed, you won't know just how wrong you are until you witness the ultimate war between heaven and hell in this supernaturally charged thriller that re-teams Hellraiser: Deader co-stars Kari Wuhrer and Doug Bradley. When an ancient, self-generating religious manuscript known as The Lexicon lands in the hands of an unsuspecting young woman, she is horrified to learn that the mysterious text continues to write itself -- forever revealing future predictions that, if discovered, could alter the course of history. Caught in an epic supernatural battle between fearless renegade angels determined to use the monolithic revelations of The Lexicon to achieve their own nefarious means, the young woman must protect the ancient text or risk eternal damnation for all of humankind(n)

programme.title: Flight of the Phoenix
programme.desc: Based on a novel by Elleston Trevor, director John Moore's The Flight of the Phoenix is a remake of a 1965 film of the same name starring film icon James Stewart. The story revolves around the plight of Captain Frank Towns (Dennis Quaid), a pilot whose C-119 cargo plane full of oil workers could not withstand the violent winds of a desert sandstorm. Stranded in the harsh terrain of Mongolia's Gobi Desert (a departure from the original, in which the plane crashed in the Sahara), Frank and his navigator face an equal challenge in maintaining order among the survivors. The group of oilmen had planned on an uneventful trip to shut off a group of rigs falling below their productivity expectations -- not fending for their very lives. Before long, some men are revealed as cowards, while others exhibit a surprising show of strength, all the while hoping that the wreckage of the original plane can be salvaged before a Lord of the Flies situation occurs. Miranda Otto is featured in a supporting role, as well as Giovanni Ribisi and Tyrese Gibson(n)

programme.title: The Simpsons
programme.desc: The Last Temptation of Krust. A veritable who's who of famous comedians have come to Springfield for a special fund-raising event, but Bart Simpson (voice of Nancy Cartwright) is appalled to discover that local legend Krusty the Clown (voice of Dan Castellaneta) hasn't been added to the bill. Bart persuades organizer and headliner Jay Leno to give Krusty a spot in the show, but the clown's offensive and out-of-date material goes over like a lead balloon, and subsequent attempts by Krusty to juice up his act fail miserably. Convinced he spent more time on marketing than material, Krusty decides to retire, but in his farewell show, he delivers a venomous screed against the current state of comedy and television that brings down the house. It becomes clear the world wants an angrier and edgier Krusty, and the clown works up a new act to match his new image. However, when a pair of auto company admen ask Krusty to endorse a new sport utility vehicle, the clown's rejection of corporate culture proves to be short-lived. "The Last Temptation of Krust" features voice cameos from Jay Leno, Steven Wright, Janeane Garofalo, Bobcat Goldthwait and Bruce Baum, all appearing as themselves, while Hank Williams Jr. contributes the SUV jingle. programme.desc: Edmund receives a visit from the bloodthirsty Bishop of Bath and Wells, who threatens to do him a mischief with a red-hot poker over the matter of an unpaid loan. programme.title: Blackadder
programme.desc: Lord Melchett challenges Edmund to a drinking contest that he cannot get out of - but his puritanical uncle and aunt Lord and Lady Whiteadder are visiting on the same night, leaving him trying to be in two places at once. Comedy, guest starring Miriam Margolyes, with Rowan Atkinson and Stephen Fry.(n)

programme.title: House of Fools
programme.desc: Vic and Bob are struggling to find a plot for this episode, but things look up when letter arrives from the White House announcing a surprise visit to their household. Beef brings over his truth-telling turban for everyone to try on, while a health inspector threatens to close down Julie's bistro when Bosh unwittingly reveals the state of the kitchen. Comedy, starring Vic Reeves and Bob Mortimer.(n)

programme.title: House of Fools
programme.desc: Vic prepares for a big date with his ex-girlfriend Mary, but she has to cancel at the last minute so his friends set about concocting an ingenious plan to make sure he isn't left disappointed. Julie's disguise and Beef's magical time-stopping whip ensure the rendezvous goes ahead, but when the truth is finally revealed, Vic's reaction is not what anyone had expected. Comedy guest starring Sally Phillips, with Vic Reeves and Bob Mortimer.(n)

programme.title: The League of Gentlemen
programme.desc: Fired from his job, Geoff leaves his life in plastic-injection mouldings for the heady world of the London stand-up comedy scene. Meanwhile, Legz Akimbo theatre company mounts its latest production - a sensitive look at the disabled - and Tish descends on Camden Town. Award-winning cult comedy, with Mark Gatiss, Reece Shearsmith and Steve Pemberton.(n)

programme.title: River Cottage

programme.title: Drumline
programme.desc: After decades of movies about college sports, the bands who take the field at halftime finally get their day in the sun in this musical comedy drama. Devon Miles (Nick Cannon) is a talented young percussionist from Harlem who wins a music scholarship to Atlanta A & T, a prestigious African-American university. For years, Atlanta A & T has won awards for their show-style marching band, who combine expert musicianship (incorporating funk, R&B, and jazz rhythms into the traditional marching band repertoire) with choreography, dancing cheerleaders, and roof-raising showmanship. Dr. Aaron Lee (Orlando Jones), the school's band director, gives Devon a spot in the marching band's drumline, the heart and soul of a show-style band, but discovers Devon's previous musical education hardly meets his usual standard when he learns that his new drummer can't read music. Devon soon earns a reputation as a stubborn individualist within the band, not necessarily a good thing in an ensemble where a strictly unified performance is considers the ideal. Devon's cocksure attitude and streetwise style doesn't mesh very comfortably with Sean Taylor (Leonard Roberts), a disciplined senior who resents the presence of the upstart freshman in the drumline, and things become even less harmonious when Devon begins making a play for Laila (Zoe Saldana), a beautiful girl who is also being courted by Sean. Songwriter and record producer Dallas Austin, who has worked with Boyz II Men, TLC, and Pink, served as executive producer for Drumline, helped produce the film's musical score, and contributed his own experiences as a marching band member to the screenplay(n)

programme.title: Georgia Rule
programme.desc: Jane Fonda, Felicity Huffman, and Lindsay Lohan star in director Garry Marshall's tale of a rebellious young woman who is sent to spend the summer with her grandmother when her frustrated mother fails to find a means of curbing her unruly behavior. Rachel (Lohan) is an out-of-control teen whose reckless drinking, foul mouth, and hysterical fits have become a constant source of embarrassment for her long-suffering mother, Lily (Huffman). When Rachel crashes her car, Lily determines that the only way to tame her savage daughter is to take her as far away from San Francisco as possible. Though Lily had once sworn never to return to the Idaho farm presided over by her demanding mother, Georgia (Jane Fonda), desperation has a funny way of dulling the pains of the past, and it's not long before Lily is packing Rachel in the car and setting out for potato country. Contrary to the common image of the sweet and doting grandmother, Georgia is a stern matriarch whose beliefs in the power of God and a hard day's work stand in stark contrast to the carefree lifestyle of the tempestuous Rachel. An interesting thing happens as the summer wears on, though; despite her initial efforts to disrupt the quiet Mormon community, Rachel's rage is gradually tempered as she learns the value of structure and responsibility. Later, as Rachel's protective walls begin to crumble and she begins to embrace compassion and kindness, the doors are opened for three generations of family to confront the long-buried secrets of their past and finally move forward in the healing process(n)

programme.desc: Hairdresser Julie hosts the first of a week of dinner parties in Co Durham, hoping to win over her guests with a no-nonsense menu she can prepare in advance. Alliances are quickly forged when David and Tina discover they both love a good gossip, before they turn their attention to Stephen when David compares him to a tramp. Julie overcooks her beef, but will her hosting make up for it and bag her the £1,000 prize?.(n)

programme.title: Come Dine with Me
programme.desc: Beauty teacher Ashleigh throws the second of the week's parties in Co Durham, she hopes a menu of sophisticated dishes - along with a helping of hearts and love - will help her win the cash prize. programme.title: Come Dine with Me
programme.desc: Call centre complaints officer and part-time farmer Stephen hosts the third night of a week of dinner parties in Co Durham. programme.title: Come Dine with Me

programme.title: A Place in the Sun: Winter Sun

programme.title: Walking Through History
programme.sub-title: Walking Through History: King John's Ruin - Peak District.
programme.desc: As the 800th anniversary of the signing of Magna Carta in June 1215 approaches, Tony Robinson sets out to discover the real King John. His walk across the medieval monarch's stamping grounds of Sherwood Forest and the Peak District reveals a hapless man stumbling from crisis to crisis who, in the end, had no choice but to sign away some of his power. In the midst of what are now cultivated fields, Tony finds the scant remains of Laxton Castle, once the control centre where strict `forest law' was administered and where taxes and fines flooded into the royal coffers. Later, in Sherwood, he explores how the myth of Robin Hood has helped to skew the public's image of King John.(n)

programme.title: Four in a Bed
programme.desc: B&B owners take it in turns as hosts to decide which of their establishments provides the best value for money. Margaret Lofthouse and Janet Sutton, owners of The Avenue Hotel in Lancashire, hope their northern charm will appease disgruntled guests. In Penrith, Mary and Graham Walker's The Llamas Pyjamas has unusual themed sleeping quarters, while the Kallacliff in Newquay is owned by Liz Hall and Colin Eadie, who are rookies in the business. The final B&B is the One 4 Two in Bude - a love nest set up by Kathy Lawrence.(n)

programme.title: Four in a Bed
programme.desc: The owners of the Edenmore Guest House in Ardrossan, Scotland, Grassington Lodge in North Yorkshire, Manor Farm in Oxfordshire and the George and Dragon in Buckinghamshire compete. programme.title: Four in a Bed
programme.desc: The competition begins at 20 Albany Street in Edinburgh, where Denise Walker hopes her B&B will impress her fellow competitors, while the second visit is to Tom and Angela Jones's Highland Guest House in Callander, Stirling. programme.title: Four in a Bed
programme.desc: B&B owners take it in turns as hosts to decide which of their establishments provides the best value for money. The contest begins in Thame, Oxfordshire, where Langsmeade Guesthouse operators Marianne Aben and Fran Birchwood are both pleased and bemused with the feedback they receive. At Stratford House in Stratford-upon-Avon, some guests are not too impressed with hosts Natasha and Dai Pollock's children being present at breakfast. Then at the Edmund Guest House in Deal, Kent, tensions rise between Mark Genders and hosts Michael and Lorna Prime and strain on the group is magnified on the final visit to the Five Bells in Berkshire, when Michael and Lorna are underwhelmed by Mark Genders' pub B&B.(n)

programme.title: Come Dine with Me

programme.title: Come Dine with Me
programme.desc: Funeral service manager Peter Pickering hosts the second dinner party in Northamptonshire, hoping his traditional approach will win him the £1,000 cash prize. However, one guest does not like bread and butter pudding, and Stephanie is horrified by Jules's shocking revelation.(n)

programme.title: Come Dine with Me

programme.title: Come Dine with Me

programme.title: Come Dine with Me

Inspired by memories of a childhood holiday on the Isle of Man, Alison sets out meet some of the people who live on the UK's 267 inhabited islands. programme.title: Death Becomes Her
programme.desc: Two romantic rivals are both granted the secret of eternal youth by a mysterious mystic. However, as they battle to get their claws into a plastic surgeon, they discover their now-immortal bodies are capable of taking whatever damage they can dish out. Black comedy fantasy, starring Goldie Hawn, Meryl Streep, Bruce Willis and Isabella Rossellini.(n)

programme.title: The Top Ten Show 2016
programme.desc: Countdown of the biggest box office hits in Britain and America.(n)

programme.title: Vijay and I
programme.desc: A series of coincidences leads to fading actor Will being declared dead. Curious to find out what people really think of him, he decides to maintain the illusion of his demise and attend his own funeral, with the help of his best friend Rad, an Indian restaurant-owner. Transformed into a handsome and elegant Sikh, complete with turban and beard, Will takes on the persona of an old friend, Vijay, to attend the funeral, where he discovers some embarrassing truths about himself. Comedy, starring Moritz Bleibtreu, Patricia Arquette and Danny Pudi.(n)

programme.title: Nutty Professor II: The Klumps
programme.desc: Bumbling scientist Sherman Klump is engaged to be married and determined to rid himself of his troublesome alter ego Buddy Love for ever. All his problems look set to be solved by his fiancee's latest DNA experiment - but things are about to spiral out of control. Comedy sequel, starring Eddie Murphy in multiple roles, along with Janet Jackson and Larry Miller.(n)

programme.title: Mr Woodcock
programme.desc: The successful author of a self-help book has managed to put the painful memories of being bullied by his PE teacher as a chubby youngster behind him. However, when he returns to his home town to accept a prestigious award, the writer is horrified to discover his mother is planning to marry his childhood tormentor. Comedy, starring Billy Bob Thornton, Seann William Scott and Susan Sarandon.(n)

programme.title: Into the Woods: Stage to Screen
programme.desc: Behind the scenes on the movie adaptation of Stephen Sondheim's musical fairytale. With contributions from stars Meryl Streep and James Corden.(n)

programme.title: The Intern
programme.desc: A retiree grows tired of the quiet life and becomes an intern at a start-up run by a beautiful entrepreneur, and teaches the young staff a few things about successful business. Comedy, starring Robert De Niro, Anne Hathaway and Rene Russo.(n)

programme.title: Bruce Almighty
programme.desc: God tires of a down-on-his-luck reporter's constant complaining, so passes on His powers to give him a taste of ultimate responsibility. The newsman falls in love with his extraordinary abilities - but a never-ending stream of incoming prayers and his ambitious attempt to please everyone soon prove there is more to the job than meets the eye. Comedy, starring Jim Carrey, Jennifer Aniston and Morgan Freeman.(n)

programme.title: Office Space
programme.desc: A jaded computer programmer goes to bizarre lengths to get fired from his dull job - but his new laid-back attitude leads to unexpected promotions as his arrogance is taken for supreme self-confidence by unwitting bosses. Satirical comedy, starring Ron Livingston, Jennifer Aniston, Ajay Naidu and Gary Cole.(n)

programme.title: Bad Words
programme.desc: Jason Bateman directs and stars in this dark comedy about a 40-year-old misanthrope who enters children's spelling contests. With Kathryn Hahn, Rohan Chand and Philip Baker Hall.(n)

programme.title: The Intern
programme.desc: A retiree grows tired of the quiet life and becomes an intern at a start-up run by a beautiful entrepreneur, and teaches the young staff a few things about successful business. Comedy, starring Robert De Niro, Anne Hathaway and Rene Russo.(n)

programme.title: The Hangover
programme.desc: Three men on a stag weekend in Las Vegas wake up after a night of heavy drinking and find they have not only misplaced the groom, but somehow gained a tiger and a baby. Unable to remember the details of the night before, they set about piecing the clues together in the hope of finding their missing friend. Comedy, starring Bradley Cooper, Ed Helms and Zach Galifianakis.(n)

programme.title: Search Party
programme.desc: Distraught over the realization that they scared away their best friend's fiancee, two hard-partying pals set out on a wild journey to reunite the estranged couple by any means necessary. Comedy, starring Adam Pally, TJ Miller and Thomas Middleditch.(n)

programme.title: Team America: World Police
programme.desc: An American counter-terrorism unit travels around the world on the lookout for threats to global peace, causing much destruction to major world cities in the process. The biggest current menace is North Korean leader Kim Jong-il and an organisation much closer to home - the Film Actors Guild. Satirical puppet comedy, voiced by South Park creators Trey Parker and Matt Stone.(n)

programme.title: Cop Out
programme.desc: Despite working together for nine years, police partners Jimmy and Paul frequently struggle to get along. When Paul's erratic behaviour leads to the pair being suspended without pay, Jimmy is forced to sell a rare baseball card to raise funds for his daughter's wedding. However, when the collector selling the item is robbed, the duo team up to recover the memorabilia. Action comedy, starring Bruce Willis, Tracy Morgan, Juan Carlos Hernandez, Cory Fernandez and Ana de la Reguera.(n)

programme.title: Big Hero 6 Special
programme.desc: Alex Zane visits Disney studios to go behind the scenes of the animated adventure about a boy and his robot who join a team of superheroes.(n)

programme.title: Mountain Men
programme.desc: Two estranged brothers find themselves trapped together on a snowy mountain after they try and evict a squatter from a family cabin. Comedy drama, starring Chace Crawford, Tyler Labine and Britt Irvin.(n)

programme.title: What About Bob
programme.desc: A psychiatrist takes on a friend's client, who turns out to be a well-meaning but annoying neurotic barely able to leave his home. The patient is hugely impressed by the consultant's methods, leading him to follow the therapist on holiday, where he unwittingly proceeds to make his life hell while winning over his family. Comedy, starring Bill Murray, Richard Dreyfuss, Julie Hagerty and Charlie Korsmo.(n)

programme.title: The Naked Gun 2 1/2: The Smell of Fear
programme.desc: Blundering cop Frank Drebin discovers a secret conspiracy to kidnap a renowned solar energy expert and replace him with an imposter. As he sets out to bring the perpetrators to justice, he is unexpectedly reunited with an old flame. Slapstick comedy sequel, starring Leslie Nielsen, Priscilla Presley, George Kennedy, Richard Griffiths and OJ Simpson.(n)

programme.title: The Naked Gun 33 1/3: The Final Insult
programme.desc: Inept police detective Frank Drebin plans to retire from the force, but is lured back by the opportunity to foil a terrorist plot. Going undercover in prison, he sets out to prevent an evil mastermind from escaping and carrying out his fiendish plan - to bomb the Oscar awards ceremony. Comedy sequel, starring Leslie Nielsen, Priscilla Presley, OJ Simpson, George Kennedy and Fred Ward.(n)

programme.title: Sisters
programme.desc: Two estranged sisters are reunited when their parents decide to sell the house they grew up in. They return to the family home to clear out their childhood bedrooms, but with their parents away, seize the chance to relive their teenage years and throw one last wild house party. Comedy, starring Amy Poehler, Tina Fey and Dianne Wiest.(n)

programme.title: Trainwreck
programme.desc: A journalist lives her life by her father's maxim that monogamy never works, and has spent her adult life enjoying freedom from commitment. When she is sent to interview a doctor, an attraction develops between them, and she begins to wonder if there mighty be something to be said for a stable relationship. Comedy, starring Amy Schumer, Bill Hader, Brie Larson and Tilda Swinton.(n)

programme.title: When Harry Met Sally
programme.desc: A man and a woman with different attitudes to life meet by chance and develop a close and long-lasting friendship. But over time, a mutual sexual attraction begins to develop and threatens to ruin their relationship - raising the question whether men and women can ever really be just friends. Romantic comedy, starring Billy Crystal and Meg Ryan.(n)

programme.title: Unfinished Business
programme.desc: A small business owner and his two associates travel to Germany to seal an important deal, but a series of events conspire to make their trip a disaster - but it's coming face to face with a vicious former boss that really turns it into a nightmare. Comedy, starring Vince Vaughn, Tom Wilkinson and Dave Franco.(n)

Animated adventure, with the voices of Jim Cummings and John Fiedler.(n)

Sci-fi adventure based on James Dashner's novel, starring Dylan O'Brien, Kaya Scodelario and Patricia Clarkson.(n)

programme.title: Father of the Bride

Sci-fi thriller, with Bruce Willis, Ben Affleck, Liv Tyler, Michael Clarke Duncan, Billy Bob Thornton and Steve Buscemi.(n)

programme.title: Minority Report
programme.desc: Cop John Anderton is forced to go on the run when a supposedly infallible trio of psychics foretell he is about to kill a man he has never heard of. Convinced their prediction is false, he kidnaps one of the so-called precogs to prove his innocence - and stumbles across a complex conspiracy. Steven Spielberg's futuristic thriller, starring Tom Cruise, Colin Farrell, Samantha Morton and Max von Sydow.(n)

programme.title: Narcopolis
programme.desc: World-weary cop Frank Grieves struggles to maintain law and order in a city where all forms of recreational narcotics have been made legal. While investigating the identity of an anonymous corpse, Frank is suddenly told to abandon the case, but when he refuses, he uncovers a conspiracy that sheds light on the true price of widespread legalisation. Dystopian sci-fi thriller, starring Elliot Cowan and Jonathan Pryce.(n)

programme.title: The Martian
programme.desc: A manned mission to Mars is abruptly abandoned, with one crew member left for dead. However, the astronaut has survived and faces a series of challenges - to contact Earth and arrange his rescue and to survive for the years it will take for a spacecraft to reach him on resources intended to last a month. Ridley Scott's sci-fi drama based on the novel by Andy Weir, starring Matt Damon, Jessica Chastain, Kristen Wiig and Chiwetel Ejiofor.(n)

Sadly, the scheme takes a disturbing turn when a deranged stalker breaks into her home before subjecting her to a terrifying ordeal. Horror, starring Ali Cobrin, Adam DiMarco and Slaine.(n)

programme.desc: A deep space search and rescue team is sent to a mining colony on an alien world that has been devastated by a viral outbreak on a mission to find and bring back the only survivor. The crew discovers a powerful weapon that poses a threat to all life on Earth. Sci-fi thriller, starring Daniel MacPherson and Grace Huang.(n)

programme.title: Little Shop of Horrors
programme.desc: A weedy flower-shop assistant grows a bizarre plant, which he discovers needs to feed on human blood to survive. It grows to a vast size and begins to talk, demanding he commit murder on its behalf. Comedy musical based on the Broadway show, starring Rick Moranis, Ellen Greene, Steve Martin and Bill Murray, with the voice of The Four Tops' Levi Stubbs.(n)

programme.title: Suicide Squad: DC Villains Uncovered
programme.desc: The latest blockbuster from DC sees a group of super villains thrown together to save the world. This documentary catches up with those responsible for making bad guys look good.(n)

programme.title: Star Trek: The Motion Picture
programme.desc: A mysterious, planet-sized energy cloud is heading for Earth, destroying everything in its path. Admiral James T Kirk returns to the bridge of the Enterprise to stop the invader, but he has to contend with a bitter rival and the possession of one of his crew by the alien force. Sci-fi adventure, the first movie based on the TV series, starring William Shatner, Leonard Nimoy, DeForest Kelley and Persis Khambatta.(n)

programme.title: Star Trek II: The Wrath of Khan
programme.desc: The Enterprise crew faces a bitter battle to the death with an old enemy. Khan, a genetically engineered superhuman tyrant, has escaped exile on a barren planet and hijacked a starship to take his revenge on Admiral Kirk, while also scheming to turn an experimental planet-creating device into a doomsday weapon. Sci-fi adventure sequel, with William Shatner, Leonard Nimoy, Ricardo Montalban and Kirstie Alley.(n)

programme.title: Star Trek III: The Search for Spock
programme.desc: Admiral Kirk and his crew hijack the decommissioned Enterprise to recover the body of their fallen comrade Mr Spock from the planet Genesis. Kirk has learnt that Spock's spirit is still alive, and the Vulcan can be resurrected, but he must also battle a Klingon captain determined to control the planet's mysterious energy. Sci-fi sequel, directed by Leonard Nimoy, with William Shatner, DeForest Kelley and Christopher Lloyd.(n)

programme.title: Star Trek IV: The Voyage Home
programme.desc: The Enterprise crew travels back in time to prevent an alien probe destroying the Earth. The only thing that can avert the disaster is a humpback whale, a creature extinct in the 23rd century - but adjusting to life back in 1986 proves a distinct challenge. Sci-fi adventure sequel, starring William Shatner, DeForest Kelley and Leonard Nimoy, who also directed.(n)

programme.title: Star Trek V: The Final Frontier
programme.desc: The Starship Enterprise races to the rescue of intergalactic ambassadors held hostage on a distant planet. The crisis proves to be the handiwork of a renegade Vulcan mystic who kidnaps Captain Kirk and his crew, ordering them to fly to an unexplored world where he hopes to fulfil his insane ambition - to meet God. Sci-fi adventure, written, directed by and starring William Shatner, with Leonard Nimoy, DeForest Kelley and David Warner.(n)

programme.title: Star Trek VI: The Undiscovered Country
programme.desc: Captain Kirk is framed for the assassination of the Klingon head of state just as the Federation is about to make peace with their old enemies. As Kirk and Dr McCoy are banished to an icy prison planet, Spock tries to uncover the identity of the real killers. Sci-fi adventure sequel, with William Shatner, Leonard Nimoy, DeForest Kelley, Christopher Plummer, with appearances by Christian Slater and Michael Dorn from Star Trek: The Next Generation.(n)

programme.title: Star Trek: Generations
programme.desc: USS Enterprise Captain Jean-Luc Picard must stop a deranged genius obsessed with gaining access to a mysterious energy source - regardless of the threat to entire civilisations that lie in his path. Help arrives from an unlikely quarter - his supposedly long dead predecessor Captain James T Kirk. Sci-fi adventure sequel, starring Patrick Stewart, William Shatner, Malcolm McDowell and Whoopi Goldberg.(n)

programme.title: Star Trek: First Contact
programme.desc: Captain Jean-Luc Picard and the crew of the Enterprise face their deadliest enemies, the Borg, who travel back in time in an attempt to change Earth's history. The starship follows on a mission to foil their plan, but the vessel is taken over by members of the cyborg collective, leaving Picard consumed by a desire for revenge. Sci-fi adventure sequel, starring Patrick Stewart, Jonathan Frakes, Brent Spiner, James Cromwell and Alice Krige.(n)

programme.title: Star Trek: Insurrection
programme.desc: Captain Picard and the Enterprise crew uncover a conspiracy by their own superiors and a sinister alien race to take over a peaceful world and exploit its power to prolong life. However, the crew is forced to defy Federation orders and turns renegade to protect the planet's inhabitants. Sci-fi adventure sequel, starring Patrick Stewart, F Murray Abraham, Jonathan Frakes, Brent Spiner and Michael Dorn.(n)

programme.title: Alone in the Dark
programme.desc: An otherworldly investigator learns of a secret which could mean the end of civilization as we know it in this thriller based on the popular video game *Alone in the Dark. Edward Carnby (Christian Slater) is a detective with Bureau 713, a secret investigative team affiliated with the United States government that explores supernatural and paranormal events. One of Carnby's assignments leads him to discover the secrets of the Abskani, an ancient tribe that worshiped demonic forces which gave them incredible powers. Carnby's findings suggest that the Abskani are poised to return to take over the world, and only one person has the knowledge to stop them -- archeologist Aline Cedrac (Tara Reid), who happens to be Carnby's former girlfriend. But Carnby's psyche has been tainted by his encounter with the Abskani demons, and he must now fight against their attempts to take over his mind as well as their attempts to conquer the Earth. Alone in the Dark also stars Stephen Dorff, Will Sanderson, and Françoise Yip(n)

programme.desc: Jake Gyllenhaal stars as troubled boxer Billy Hope in this high-stakes drama from director Antoine Fuqua and Sons of Anarachy creator Kurt Sutter. At the height of his fame and success, Hope is convinced by his loving wife Maureen (Rachel McAdams) to retire from the sport in order to spend more time with the couple's daughter Leila (Oona Laurence). On the night of his retirement announcement, a rival boxer calls out Hope and an altercation breaks out, killing Maureen. Hope's self-destructive behavior worsens, and Leila is taken away by child services. In order to redeem his life and get his daughter back, Hope must return to boxing under the tutelage of hardened trainer Titus "Tick" Willis (Forest Whitaker)(n)

programme.desc: Directed by Spike Lee, She Hate Me follows John Henry "Jack" Armstrong (Anthony Mackie), who is fired from a posh job in biotechnology after informing the proper authorities of some sketchy business dealings from within the company. Unemployed and desperate for some quick cash, Jack accepts a strange offer -- his ex-girlfriend Fatima (Kerry Washington) says she will pay him generously if he successfully impregnates her. Once word gets out among the lesbian community, Jack is inundated with requests, and is initially quite happy with his new direction in life. However, things -- as they are wont to do -- get complicated. There's his former employer, who is actively trying to pin the blame for their wrongdoings on his shoulders, for one thing, and it isn't long before the moral implications of his life as a sperm donor come to the forefront. The film co-stars John Turturro, Ellen Barkin, Woody Harrelson, Monica Bellucci, and Q-Tip(n)

programme.title: Kate & Leopold
programme.desc: X-Men star Hugh Jackman is entranced by modern girl Meg Ryan in this charming, fantastical romantic comedy. A female executive has left little time in her busy life for romance, until her ex-boyfriend opens up a time portal which transports a charming nineteenth-century bachelor to 21st-century America. A mutual attraction soon develops between the suave European aristocrat and the liberated career woman(n)
